<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Lightness" class="currentChild" href="Lightness">Lightness</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
One of the three basic qualities of a color on most <a title="Color Model" href="Color_Model">color model</a>s, describing the degree of darkness or brightness of a particular color, plotted on most three-dimensional color coordinate systems independently of <a title="Hue" href="Hue">hue</a> and <a title="Saturation" href="Saturation">saturation</a>. See <a title="CIE Color Space" href="CIE_Color_Space">CIE Color Space</a>, for example. 
</p>
<p id="l3">
'Lightness<em> also refers to the general brightness or darkness of a black-and-white or color image in general. 
</p>
